1. PRODUCT GOAL
====================================================================

Build a controlled browser-automation product that demonstrates this exact
end-to-end loop:

1. User enters a supported natural-language intent.
2. System produces a typed business-flow plan.
3. User selects a visible UI mutation in a graphical “UI Change Lab.”
4. The selected mutation changes the actual controlled storefront.
5. System runs the original Playwright regression test.
6. Deliberate UI change breaks the original brittle locator.
7. System captures failed step, error, screenshot, and trace where possible.
8. System diagnoses the reason for failure.
9. System proposes a safe semantic locator repair.
10. User explicitly approves or rejects that repair.
11. System deterministically validates approved repair.
12. System reruns the complete journey.
13. System displays final status: HEALED only when full rerun succeeds.

Primary product claim:

“A controlled UI change breaks a browser test; TestPilot captures evidence,
proposes a repair, requires human approval, validates the repair, and restores
the full business journey.”

